title: Что такое CORS – Telegraph
og:title: Что такое CORS
og:description:
CORS расшифровывается как Cross-Origin Resource Sharing. Это механизм браузера, который позволяет определить список ресурсов, к которым страница может получить доступ. Он необходим для обеспечения безопасности и защиты пользователей от злоумышленников при использовании HTTP протокола.
По умолчанию, сайты могут запрашивать ресурсы только со своего origin. Такое ограничение называется Same-Origin Policy. CORS расширяет Same-Origin Policy, позволяя получать доступ к ресурсам с разных доменов.

og:description:
1. Console.log - обычная команда, которая показывает всё-что вы введёте. К примеру введём надпись "Hello World". 
2. Console.error - то же самое, что и консоль, разве что выдаёт ошибки. Помещает их определённым образом. К примеру "File Not Found".
3. Console.info - Вводит информацию, которую вы ввели. В принципе ничем не отличается.
4. Console.clear - просто отчистка консоли.
5. Console.warn - Это предупреждение, которое также может быть любым.

Атрибут `sandbox` используется для ограничения выполнения JavaScript в элементе `iframe`. Это может быть полезно для безопасного встраивания сторонних контентов.
```html
<iframe src="https://example.com" sandbox="allow-scripts"></iframe>
```

`scope` применяется к элементам таблицы (`<th>`) и определяет, к каким ячейкам таблицы относится заголовок. Это улучшает доступность таблиц для скринридеров.

В случае если она не работает, то скорее всего функция отключена в настройках браузера, например в Хроме можно найти данный пункт в поиске по запросу «Проверка правописания».

Управление правописанием в полях
Если в вашей форме нужно принудительно отключить проверку правописания, то к элементу нужно добавить атрибут spellcheck="false", например:
<textarea spellcheck="false"></textarea>…

og:title: Sending Email Using Node.js — SitePoint

og:title: The Best Award-Winning Websites To Use As Inspiration
og:description: Discover award-winning websites that set the standard for creativity, usability, and design excellence. Get inspired for your next project.

title: Colorful Blossoms And Rainy Days (April 2024 Wallpapers Edition) — Smashing Magazine
og:title: Colorful Blossoms And Rainy Days (April 2024 Wallpapers Edition) — Smashing Magazine
og:description: Could there be a better way to welcome the new month than with a little inspiration boost? We might have one for you: desktop wallpapers created by the community for the community. Enjoy!

title: Setting And Persisting Color Scheme Preferences With CSS And A “Touch” Of JavaScript — Smashing Magazine
og:title: Setting And Persisting Color Scheme Preferences With CSS And A “Touch” Of JavaScript — Smashing Magazine
og:description: There are many ways to approach a “Dark Mode” feature that respects a user’s system color scheme preferences and allows for per-site customization. Henry Bley-Vroman walks through a new possibility that leans into cutting-edge CSS, with minimal JavaScript to support persisting the user’s color scheme preference across pages.

title: Connecting With Users: Applying Principles Of Communication To UX Research — Smashing Magazine
og:title: Connecting With Users: Applying Principles Of Communication To UX Research — Smashing Magazine
og:description: Victor Yocco reviews the components of the Transactional Model of communication, explaining how we might apply this framework to preparing, conducting, and analysing our UX research. You will understand how many UX research best practices align with the model and get an example of a tool for tracking alignment.

title: Converting Plain Text To Encoded HTML With Vanilla JavaScript — Smashing Magazine
og:title: Converting Plain Text To Encoded HTML With Vanilla JavaScript — Smashing Magazine
og:description: What do you do when you need to convert plain text into formatted HTML? Perhaps you reach for Markdown or manually write in the element tags yourself. Or maybe you have one or two of the dozens of online tools that will do it for you. In this tutorial, Alexis Kypridemos picks those tools apart and details the steps for how we can do it ourselves with a little vanilla HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.

title: Iconography In Design Systems: Easy Troubleshooting And Maintenance — Smashing Magazine
og:title: Iconography In Design Systems: Easy Troubleshooting And Maintenance — Smashing Magazine
og:description: Tatsiana Tarkan digs deep into iconography as part of a design system and shares some doable tips that will turn icon creation and maintenance into an enjoyable process.

title: Infinite-Scrolling Logos In Flat HTML And Pure CSS — Smashing Magazine
og:title: Infinite-Scrolling Logos In Flat HTML And Pure CSS — Smashing Magazine
og:description: Remember the HTML `` element? It’s deprecated, so it’s not like you’re going to use it when you need some sort of horizontal auto-scrolling feature. That’s where CSS comes in because it has all the tools we need to pull it off. Silvestar Bistrović demonstrates a technique that makes it possible with a set of images and as little HTML as possible.

title: How To Monitor And Optimize Google Core Web Vitals — Smashing Magazine
og:title: How To Monitor And Optimize Google Core Web Vitals — Smashing Magazine
og:description: The three Core Web Vitals metrics don’t only tell you how visitors experience your website but also impact your Google search result rankings. In this article, we’ll look at what Core Web Vitals are, how they are measured, and how you can use DebugBear to monitor them continuously.

title: Penpot’s CSS Grid Layout: Designing With Superpowers — Smashing Magazine
og:title: Penpot’s CSS Grid Layout: Designing With Superpowers — Smashing Magazine
og:description: Penpot helps designers and developers work better together by offering a free, open-source design tool based on open web standards. Today, let's explore Penpot’s latest feature, CSS Grid Layout. Penpot’s latest release is about efficiency and so much more. It gives designers superpowers and a better place at the table. Excited? Let’s take a look at it together.

title: Sliding 3D Image Frames In CSS — Smashing Magazine
og:title: Sliding 3D Image Frames In CSS — Smashing Magazine
og:description: Creating 3D effects in CSS isn’t an entirely new concept, but typical approaches use additional elements in the markup and pseudo-elements in the styles to pull it off. Temani Afif applies 3D effects and sliding transitions to a single `` using clever CSS techniques that demonstrate advanced, modern styling practices.

title: The Things Users Would Appreciate In Mobile Apps — Smashing Magazine
og:title: The Things Users Would Appreciate In Mobile Apps — Smashing Magazine
og:description: What can we do to make a mobile app better? What subsidiary features are worth providing for our users? I have some ideas. You might, too. So, let’s compare our notes. Without any prescriptions attached, here are seven features I believe can palpably improve a user’s experience with a mobile app.
